csDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3614795\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3614795\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nik1665703029224.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nik1665703029224.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nik1665703029224.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"nik1665703029224\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                          \n Height\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Height of the form or report, in character cells. In the Layout Editor, this is represented by a blue dashed line.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nik1665703029224__section_v2w_jbj_5wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d95376e51\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nik1665703029224__p_d100724e1_d100725e1_d100726e1\">This property does not show the size required for\n        everything to fit.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nik1665703029224__p_d100727e1_d100728e1_d100729e1\">For report components, data is expanded, and wrapped\n        according to the horizontal size of the fields defined in the report.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nik1665703029224__p_d100730e1_d100731e1_d100732e1\">For form components, the property influences the size\n        of a form at runtime, but the actual size depends on a number of factors such as the\n        geometry set in ProcScript and the value of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Font0</span> in the initialization\n        file.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nik1665703029224__p_d100733e1_d100734e1_d100735e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"olx1665702612615.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/olx1665702612615.html\" title=\"The initial size and position of a form are set in the Uniface IDE using the Height, Width, Top and Left properties in the Properties Inspector of the component. Form height and width are made visible at design time using a blue dashed bottom and right border on the Form canvas, if both Height, Width have a value &gt; 0.\">Form Size and Position</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nik1665703029224__section_gg2_lbj_5wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d95376e98\">Setting in ProcScript</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nik1665703029224__p_d100970e1_d100971e1_d100972e1\">For form components, it is possible to define the\n        geometry (size and position) as pixels in ProcScript:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"nik1665703029224__ul_if4_mbj_5wb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nik1665703029224__li_d40751e1_d40752e1_d40753e1\">When creating a new component instance by setting the\n            <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Dimension</span> property. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kfu1665702580321.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kfu1665702580321.html\" title=\"Specifies a comma-separated string that defines the position and size of the form window in pixels.\">Dimension</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ryt1665702577808.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ryt1665702577808.html\" title=\"Creates a new instance of a component.\">newinstance</a>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nik1665703029224__li_d40754e1_d40755e1_d40756e1\">Dynamically by explicitly setting\n            <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$windowproperties</span> to the desired position and dimensions. For more\n          information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bch1665702773514.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bch1665702773514.html\" title=\"Set or return the current window properties of a Form instance.\">$windowproperties</a>. <div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"nik1665703029224__note_nbl_vbj_5wb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Height</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Width</span> canvas\n            properties do not take into account the size of panel and/or menus, whereas\n              <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$windowproperties</span> does.</div></li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nik1665703029224__section_z2r_mbj_5wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d95376e154\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"nik1665703029224__ul_ecr_pbj_5wb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nik1665703029224__li_d40655e1_d40656e1_d40657e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"euw1665702582150.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/euw1665702582150.html\" title=\"A Form is a stateful presentation Component that enables users to view and modify data in a Windows or character mode application.\">Form</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nik1665703029224__li_d40658e1_d40659e1_d40660e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rvk1665702582227.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rvk1665702582227.html\" title=\"A Report is a Component that defines the content and layout of printed output of a Uniface application. It is not interactive and cannot be used to update the database.\">Report</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614795\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614795\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Height Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Height Height of the form or report, in character cells. In the Layout Editor, this is represented by a blue dashed line. Description This property does not show the size required for everything to fit. For report components, data is expanded, and wrapped according to the horizontal size of the fields defined in the report. For form components, the property influences the size of a form at runtime, but the actual size depends on a number of factors such as the geometry set in ProcScript and the value of Font0 in the initialization file. For more information, see Form Size and Position . Setting in ProcScript For form components, it is possible to define the geometry (size and position) as pixels in ProcScript: When creating a new component instance by setting the Dimension property. For more information, see Dimension and newinstance . Dynamically by explicitly setting $windowproperties to the desired position and dimensions. For more information, see $windowproperties . Note: The Height and Width canvas properties do not take into account the size of panel and/or menus, whereas $windowproperties does. Applies To Form Report Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}